<DOC><DOCNO> AP900118-0068 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-01-18-90 1023EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-People-Jagger     01-18 0172</FIRST><SECOND>PM-People-Jagger,0178</SECOND><HEAD>Mick Jagger and Longtime Companion Jerry Hall to Marry</HEAD><DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   After two kids and 12 years together, Jerry Hallsaid today that she and Rolling Stone Mick Jagger will get married.   She didn't say when _ but neither did Jagger when he announced,in 1983, that they would be tying the knot ``any day now.''   ``For the first time, we both think marriage is a good thing,''Ms. Hall told reporters at the Lyric Theater, where she will bestarring in ``Bus Stop,'' with singer Shaun Cassidy.   The Texas-born model and actress refused to confirm that herlarge diamond ring was an engagement present from the rock singer,who is in the Caribbean.   ``He gives me a ring like this about once a year,'' she said.   Hall and Jagger have two children: Elizabeth Scarlett, 5, andLeroy Augustine, 3.   Ms. Hall appeared in ``Bus Stop'' in 1988 in New Jersey, and theBritish production will open next week in suburban Watford beforemoving to London in February.</TEXT></DOC>